cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.NI, cs.PL 

The paper focuses on the security of embedded systems, specifically their web interfaces, and proposes a framework for automated vulnerability discovery through dynamic firmware analysis. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of full system emulation and analysis of network services suggests a systems and control perspective (cs.SY), while the focus on web interfaces and network devices suggests a networking and internet architecture perspective (cs.NI). Finally, the implementation of the framework involves programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
